tps://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS4_57.1541_DD_AT19_3584-tms.jpg"},{"ObjectID":8115,"Title":"T'oros Roslin Gospels","Artist":"6635|6635","Date":"1262 (Medieval)","Medium":"ink and pigments on well finished, medium weight parchment covered with brown stamped leather decorated with jeweled and nielloed metal-gilt plaques","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1935, by gift.[1] Rebound in that church in 1643.[2] Recorded in this location in 1886 and 1904. Seen at the monastery ca. 1914 by the Armenian archbishop (probably Karekin Hovsepian). The location of the manuscript is unknown between 1914 and 1931, and it may have been removed from Armenian territory at some point during World War I and the Armenian Genocide.[3] Letters in the Walters Art Museum Archives about this manuscript note that Dikran Kelekian sold the manuscript to Henry Walters in Paris in 1926, 1928, or 1929. It remained in the Walters’ personal collection until it was gifted to the Walters Art Gallery in 1935 by Mrs. Walters.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/W.539","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/CPS_W.539.binding-9_Fp_DD.jpg"},{"ObjectID":7415,"Title":"Ringing the New Year In","Artist":"4486","Date":"1810-1874","Medium":"sepia wash","CreditLine":"given to Walters Art Museum, 1977.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/37.2553.1","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS3_37.2553.1_Fnt_DD_KI13.jpg"},{"ObjectID":3915,"Title":"Book of Hours","Artist":"8629|7231","Date":"ca. 1430-1435, with additions ca. 1460","Medium":"ink and pigments on medium-weight, light-cream-colored parchment, well surfaced on both sides; miniatures on heavier parchment  between black calfskin covering beech boards; blind panel-stamping laid out in two panels on both boards, each panel displaying two vine-scrolls in mirror image of each other containing a bird, a rabbit couchant, a cock, a deer couchant, and a pelican in piety; both panels surrounded by the inscription \"\"Ora pro nobis sancta / Dei genitrix ut / digni efficamur promis / sione Xpristi\"\"; between panels a smaller compartment composed of three stamps displaying a wivern couchant, St. Margaret emerging from the dragon, and a gryphon rampant; all edges gilt;  indications of a central fastening, now a pair of late Gothic brass catch-and-strap clasps hinging from lower board","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/W.168","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/CPS_W.168.binding_TopExt_DD.jpg"},{"ObjectID":8290,"Title":"\"\"Fortification Agate\"\" Snuff Bottle","Artist":"6238","Date":"19th century","Medium":"agate","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/41.179","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS1_41.179_VwA_DD_AT18-032538-tms.jpg"},{"ObjectID":590,"Title":"Adoration of the Magi","Artist":"6211","Date":"mid 13th century","Medium":"ink and pigments on thick parchment","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/W.78.1V","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/CPS_W.78.1V_Fp_DD.jpg"},{"ObjectID":6715,"Title":"Baluster-Shaped Vase","Artist":"6238","Date":"1736-1795 (Qing dynasty (1644-1911))","Medium":"porcelain with copper red glaze","CreditLine":"by bequest to Walters Art Museum, 1931.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/49.529","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS1_49.529_SideA_DD_T17-tms.jpg"},{"ObjectID":2515,"Title":"Peasant Woman and Child","Artist":"5721","Date":"19th century","Medium":"Pencil and watercolor on paper","CreditLine":"The Walters Art Museum","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/37.1628","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PL2_37.1628_Fnt_BW_H83.jpg"},{"ObjectID":4265,"Title":"Box for the Incense Game","Artist":"6194","Date":"18th century","Medium":"black and gold lacquer over wood","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://